OL,3,C'Life changing' wearable Tourette's
OL,4,Cdevice shown to reduce tics
OL,6,FThe Channel Islands is helping fund
OL,7,Fand develop new wearable technology
OL,8,Fthat could prove life-changing for
OL,9,Fpeople living with Tourette Syndrome
OL,10,Fby reducing the frequency and severity
OL,11,Fof tics.
OL,13,FThe Neupulse medical device - created
OL,14,Fby Neurotherapeutics Ltd and
OL,15,FNottingham University - sends gentle
OL,16,Felectrical signals to the median nerve
OL,17,Fin the underside of the wrist to
OL,18,Fstimulate the area of the brain that
OL,19,Fcauses the involuntary sounds and
OL,20,Fmovements associated with the
OL,21,Fcondition.
