OL,3,C'Life changing' wearable Tourette's
OL,4,Cdevice shown to reduce tics
OL,6,FDeveloper Paul Cable told ITV Channel
OL,7,FTV: "It's not a cure for Tourette's,
OL,8,Fbut it's a tool to help manage tics. A
OL,9,Fclinical trial in 2023 showed 59% of
OL,10,Fpeople got a benefit from using the
OL,11,Fdevice.
OL,13,F"You see people change and it gets me
OL,14,Fevery time - they feel much calmer,
OL,15,Ftheir tics reduce and you see them
OL,16,Fsmile."
