OL,3,C'Life changing' wearable Tourette's
OL,4,Cdevice shown to reduce tics
OL,6,FThere is no known cure for the
OL,7,Fcondition, which affects more than
OL,8,F300,000 people in the UK, and
OL,9,Ftreatment options are typically
OL,10,Flimited to medication and behavioural
OL,11,Ftherapy.
OL,13,FTics include movements like shoulder
OL,14,Fshrugging, blinking, jerking or making
OL,15,Fnoises.
OL,17,FSwearing - known as coprolalia -
OL,18,Foccurs in only around 10% of cases,
OL,19,Fdespite being commonly associated with
OL,20,FTourette's.
